shared_text:
Most Teens Don't added 40 new photos.
February 5 at 10:21 PM ·

Today was filled with advocacy, history & fun! We began our day with a White House Tour, visited the Natural History Museum, met with a staff member at our State Representatives office, went to the top of the Washington Monument, and ended the day at the Holocaust Museum. The students then attended the CADCA youth dance to prove youth can have fun without alcohol, tobacco or other drugs. #mostteensdont #leadersoftoday

Did you know that underage drinking negatively affects your developing brain? When your cerebellum, the part of the brain responsible for coordination and speed, is impaired, it becomes harder to react quickly and efficiently.

Play this game to find out more about how alcohol can affect the brain.
